abstract_ssm: Vito Marcantonio (1902-1954), who received his law degree from New York University in 1931, was an American Labor Party leader and U.S. Congressmen representing East Harlem, New York, 1935-1937 (as a Republican), and 1939-1951 (American Labor Party). This collection contains six United States Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) files obtained under the Freedom of Information Act and one U.S. State Department document.
